  <TEXT>
    <Tag>TXT_KEY_UNIT_ARBALEST_PEDIA</Tag>
    <English>[TAB]The arbalest was a late variation of the medieval European crossbow. A larger weapon, the arbalest had a steel prod ("bow"). Since an arbalest was much larger than earlier crossbows, and because of the greater tensile strength of steel, it had a greater force and range. A skilled arbalestier could shoot two bolts per minute. Arbalests were sometimes considered inhumane or unfair weapons, since an inexperienced arbalestier could use one to kill a knight who had a lifetime of training.</English>
    <L1 />
    <L2 />
    <L3 />
    <L4 />
